ow the ideological domination of oppressed classes can shatter.This work is a new and vital chapter in the growing literature on the formation of social movements. It chronicles the transformation of Peru's poor from a culture of deference and clientelism in the late 1960s to a population mobilized for radical political action today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aConflits sociauxxPérou. 0aMouvements sociauxxPérou. 0aPauvres en milieu urbainxActivité politiquexPérou. 0aSocial conflictxPeru. 0aSocial conflictzPeru. 0aSocial movementsxPeru. 0aSocial movementszPeru. 0aUrban poorxPolitical activityxPeru. 0aUrban poorxPolitical activityzPeru. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520916234?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520916234423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520916234/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles